-- Abu Dhabi Investment House Takes Stake in Zain Saudi
-- B y   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 2012-06-06T11:37:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/abu-dhabi-s-wealth-fund-takes-stake-in-zain-saudi-argaam-says.html
(Corrects name of company in headline and story.)  Abu Dhabi Investment House has taken
a 2.14 percent stake in Mobile Telecommunications of  Saudi
Arabia , known as  Zain Saudi (ZAINKSA) ,  Argaam  reported, citing a
prospectus on the restructuring of the company’s capital.  The shares were transferred last month to Abu Dhabi
Investment House from Rakisa Holding based on a ruling by the
general public complaints office, the news portal said. Abu
Dhabi Investment House’s stake is equivalent to 30 million
shares, the newspaper said.  Kuwait-based Zain Group said it had no comment on the
report when contacted by Bloomberg News today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fiona MacDonald in Kuwait at 
 fmacdonald4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
